
===========================================================
üîê Methods in java.util.concurrent.locks.Lock (Definitions)
===========================================================

1Ô∏è‚É£ void lock()
----------------
‚Ä¢ Acquires the lock.
‚Ä¢ If the lock is already held by another thread, the current thread waits indefinitely until the lock becomes available.

2Ô∏è‚É£ void lockInterruptibly() throws InterruptedException
---------------------------------------------------------
‚Ä¢ Similar to lock(), but the waiting thread can be interrupted.
‚Ä¢ Useful when you do NOT want a thread to wait forever for a lock.

3Ô∏è‚É£ boolean tryLock()
---------------------
‚Ä¢ Attempts to acquire the lock immediately.
‚Ä¢ Returns:
      true  ‚Üí if the lock is free and acquired
      false ‚Üí if the lock is already held by another thread
‚Ä¢ Does NOT block the thread.

4Ô∏è‚É£ boolean tryLock(long time, TimeUnit unit) throws InterruptedException
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
‚Ä¢ Attempts to acquire the lock but waits only for the specified time.
‚Ä¢ If lock is acquired within the given time ‚Üí returns true
  else ‚Üí returns false.
‚Ä¢ Thread can be interrupted while waiting.

5Ô∏è‚É£ void unlock()
-----------------
‚Ä¢ Releases the lock.
‚Ä¢ MUST be called inside a finally block to avoid deadlock in case of exception.

6Ô∏è‚É£ Condition newCondition()
---------------------------
‚Ä¢ Creates a Condition object used for advanced thread communication.
‚Ä¢ Similar to wait()/notify(), but more flexible and works only with Lock implementations.
  Example: condition.await(), condition.signal()

===========================================================
Quick Summary:
--------------
lock()         ‚Üí Wait forever until lock is acquired
lockInterruptibly() ‚Üí Wait, but can be interrupted
tryLock()      ‚Üí Try immediately; do not wait
tryLock(timeout) ‚Üí Wait only for limited time
unlock()       ‚Üí Release lock
newCondition() ‚Üí Enables wait/signal style communication
===========================================================

    ‚ö° If you want quick one-liners (for revision)
    Method	                                          Meaning
1. lock()	                                    Take lock, wait forever
2. lockInterruptibly()	            Take lock, but allow interruption
3. tryLock()	                            Take lock only if free
4. tryLock(timeout)	                Take lock within given time or give up
5. unlock()	                                Release lock
6. newCondition()	                Create condition for await/signal
